The Water Department reports there's been a marked improvement in seven provinces. eNCA/Estelle Bronkhorst JOHANNESBURG - After months of dry conditions, summer rains are improving dam levels. The Water Department reports there's been a marked improvement in seven provinces. READ: Vaal Dam levels drop, government says no need to panic Gauteng levels are at 96 percent while the Eastern Cape has risen to 51 percent. Mpumalanga, KwaZulu-Natal, the North West, Northern Cape and the Free State also recorded more rainfall. Limpopo and the Western Cape showed slight declines of about 1 percent.